race.comment: TAXATION (9) was well found in betting and got the job done on debut at Hawkesbury three weeks ago, closing well to get home by a long neck over 1000m. Will enjoy the extra 100m and with some natural improvement to come he can go to this next level. KIMBERLEY SECRETS (1) had a 39-day break before a game third over this trip at Warwick Farm last time out where she led for home before being run down by a good one. At her best over 1100m and should give a great sight. MISS BUSSLINGER (2) is a talented mare back from a 20-week spell. Competitive in some good races last prep, highlighted by a close third in the Listed Daybreak Lover over 1400m. Will be better next time over more ground but watch for her late. JOISELLE (5) found one better when favourite first-up at Scone. Strips fitter and an extra 100m helps. The lightly raced filly STRADA VARENNA (6) is back for a second prep.
